title: Unemployment rate in Belgium 2019
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, containing a total of 21 data points.
Overall Unemployment rate has decreased over the Year.
The most drastic decrease took place within the Year 1999 and 2000.
Maximum Unemployment rate, about 8.65 was reported at Year 1999
The lowest Unemployment rate, of value 6.18 was reported at Year 2001
